                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="178410200055"></xptr>
            
                  <persName id="t17841020-28-person323">
                  SOLOMON
                   MARRIOTT
               <interp inst="t17841020-28-person323" type="surname" value="MARRIOTT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17841020-28-person323" type="given" value="SOLOMON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17841020-28-person323" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>On the 6th of this month, I found the prisoner on the stair-case, about two stairs up, leading to my chamber, which is up one pair of stairs, he seemed to be buckling his shoe, I watched him; I keep the house, I have no lodgers; he then picked up a bundle that lay upon the stairs, I did not not know it was my property, I was almost close by the bar, he passed the passage, and crossed the yard that leads into another passage, to go out to the Great Armoury: when he got upon the steps I thought I saw my wife's petticoat; I ran after him, a soldier that was quartered with me was there, he had the bundle, we brought him back, he said, blast your eyes, or something to that purpose; I sent for a constable, and he was sent to Bridewell.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17841020-28-person324">
                  JOHN
                   MIDDLETON
               <interp inst="t17841020-28-person324" type="surname" value="MIDDLETON"></interp>
